Our virtual book fair is going on NOW!! It will go on for the rest of the summer so everyone has a chance to get new books to read all summer long!!

Go to bookfairs.scholastic.com, click on the 'find a fair' link. Enter our school as 'exira es'. Be sure to set up an account so that your purchases benefit our school so we can earn 25% of ALL books ordered!!! Book orders can be shipped ANYWHERE in the US, so please share the info with your friends and family!! Free shipping on book orders over $25!!!!

More info available Wednesday and Thursday at computer drop off times. Keep watching for more information on social media!!!

Exira-EHK Schools
May 24 at 9:55 AM ·

Next Sunday, May 31st, will be the Spartan Graduation Parade and Drive-through ceremony. The parade will start at 1:00PM in Exira, students will travel through Brayton, Kimballton and will receive their diplomas in Elk Horn. We will release the parade route on Tuesday.

We hope you will join us to support the E-EHK graduating class of 2020. But please use social distancing to keep everyone safe.

Until then, Happy Memorial Day Weekend to our community service members. Thank you for your service! Have a fun and safe holiday.

Good Morning,
As a school district we want to abide by legal, HIPAA, and Privacy issues while still informing our communities about COVID-19 and positive cases in our area. As you may have seen the number of cases has increased recently in our surrounding communities and counties.

The Exira-EHK Community School District has learned that an individual(s) who was present at the Elk Horn school on Monday April 27th has tested positive for COVID-19.

The Public Health Department is in charge of communication with individuals who may have had contact tracing. This is within 6 feet for 30-60 minutes.

As cases continue to increase please remember to use social distancing, wear masks, and use hand sanitizer.

Thank you for understanding during this unprecedented time.

Mary Bleth-Harris
Rochelle Bruns
Trevor Miller

post_text:
Justin Brian Petersen is the son of Angie and Brian Petersen. He has one brother Travis. When Justin was younger he liked to tinker with engines in the garage. Today for fun he likes to work on pickup trucks, ride his 4-wheeler and motorcycle, and go boating-wake boarding.
The accomplishment he is most proud of in high school is receiving the FFA Blue and Gold Award for Member of the Year. Justin’s favorite memory at Exira-EHK was being part of the Trapshooting Team. Three words that best describe him are funny, positive, and hard-working. He is always willing to help a friend in need. Justin would like to be remembered as an essential worker as he leaves Exira-EHK.
Justin’s plans after high school are to attend Iowa Lake Community College for Farm Machinery and Diesel Technology. The three things he must do in this lifetime are going to Alaska, going on a moose hunt, and drag racing his diesel truck. In 5 years, Justin sees himself graduated from college and working at Robinson Implement.

Amy Marie Hartvigsen is the daughter of Kevin and Tracey Hartvigsen. Amy has one older sister Michaela and one older brother Jacob. Amy loved to go swimming at the elkhorn pool and to play sports when she was younger. Amy would like to consider herself as a tired, honest, and stubborn girl. Amy loved to sleep and party with friends in her free time. Amy is most proud of passing A & P in high school. She wishes she would have gone out for wood classes. Amy is going to miss seeing her friends every day in high school.
Amy plans to go to Iowa Central Community College in Fort Dodge, Iowa to study Radiology. Amy hopes to have traveled to Paris, get married, and have kids in the future. In 5 years, Amy sees herself owning her own house and working at a hospital.

William Winston Paulsen is the son of Alec and Cindy Paulsen. William has two younger brothers Ben and Cooper. When William was younger he enjoyed fishing at Littlefields. Fishing turned into one of Williams' passions throughout high school. William was very involved throughout high school. His favorite memory was going undefeated in powder puff volleyball during homecoming week. William wishes he would have gone out for basketball every year of high school instead of just going out Senior year. William is going to miss doing sports and seeing his friends every day after leaving high school. Three words that best describe William are tall, funny, and caring. William wants to be remembered as the guy who was always looking for a good time.
William plans to attend UNI and major in Construction/ Business Management to help expand his parent’s business. William sees himself in 5 years working with his parents somewhere near Des Moines or Omaha. William hopes to travel to every state in the U.S, go to a different country, and to have a family in his future.

He has recently started building some of his old lego kits. Cooper enjoyed time with friends. One of his favorite memories was in 5th grade. Kyla’s favorite memory she had at Exira-EHK is all the fun laughs and memories she made with her friends but during high school, Kyla wished she would’ve been more involved in Leo, 4-H or even student council. Kyla said she was going to miss the teachers and Friday Night Lights the most when she leaves Exira-EHK.
Kyla said the three things she must do in her lifetime are to teach people and help them, establish myself and be happy. Kyla sees herself in 5 years being successful.

post_text:
Creighton Emery Nelson is the son of Chris and Lindy Nelson. Creighton has an older sister Kealey and a younger brother Easton. As a child, Creighton liked to play with his friends. The friendships he made formed strong bonds in high school.
Throughout High School, Creighton ran for the school’s track team. During his freshman and sophomore year, Creighton had the chance of a lifetime to run at Drake university when the track team made it to state. Running for track and being involved in National Honors society are huge accomplishments for Creighton. High school brings plenty of opportunities for students to be involved in various things. FFA and Student council are 2 clubs that Creighton wishes to be involved in during high school.
Creighton is a tall, tan, and athletic young man. He wants to be remembered as being a great athlete. Creighton plans to graduate from Iowa Central college, own a house, and go to a different country in the near future.

Jacob James Rattenborg is the son of Joel and Stacie Hansen. Jacob is the oldest in the family with a younger brother and younger sister Matt and Paisley. As a child, Jacob liked to play outside with toy cars and ride bicycles.
High school came quick and fun for Jacob. He once deadlifted 600 in the weight room. Jacob made plenty of memories from high school. Some of his favorite times that he will miss in high school are the friendships and all of the people he has had in his high school career. Football was one of Jacob’s favorite past times throughout high school.
In his free time, Jacob likes to hunt, fish, and just enjoy being outside. After enjoying his free time, Jacob is ready to start the next step in his life. Jacob plans to join the army because he finds a passion in helping or protecting people. Jacob wants to be married, own a house, and teach others to show animals. Working hard on trucks is where Jacob wants to be in 5 years. Jacob wants to be remembered as a kind-hearted, respectful, and always ready to help others when they are in need.

Governor Kim Reynolds announced an extension of the COVID-19 shutdown for all Iowa public schools until April 30th. Consequently, all Exira-EHK School buildings and facilities will be closed until April 30th.

Exira-EHK teachers have been working hard to provide information for our students the past three weeks. Our administrative team will be meeting with the DLT team to discuss what continuous learning will look like for our students. Details about our plans will be released next week, with a target to begin online instruction for students PK-12 starting the week of April 13th. Stay tuned for more info in the next few days and STAY SAFE!

As always if you have questions please reach out to your building principals or Mr. Miller.

I hope this finds you healthy!!

Please join us in our first ever teacher parade on Friday, March 27!! We will be starting in Kimballton, traveling to Elk Horn, Exira, and ending in Brayton. Please feel free to participate in all the towns or wherever is convenient for you.

Here are the times we are planning to be in the district communities. We bare with us as we are not sure about the times. I will try to keep you updated on Facebook if we are running late/early.



Kimballton- 10:00 a.m.

Elk Horn- 10:30 a.m.-

Exira- 11:30 a.m.-

Brayton- 12:30 p.m. -

This week’s theme will be Spartan Pride so please wear your Spartan gear!

Please remember that we are practicing social distancing! Please stay 6 feet away from everyone and not to meet up with their friends/neighbors. Country kids can come to town but should not meet up at a friend's house try the park or downtown.



Hope to see you on Friday!!!

post_text:
Just a reminder for Elementary Parents

Thursday the elementary building will be open from 8:00 -12:00 for parents to come and pick up their child/children's packet that their teacher has prepared for them. These packets have conference papers as well as resources that can be used while we are not in school. 2nd-5th grade students will also be able to take their chrome books home. After Thursday there will be no access to the building for students or staff. This is the time the custodial staff will be busy deep cleaning the building. There will be no exceptions.

We ask that you come at the allotted time according to your child's last name. If you are unable to come at the allotted time you may come at a different time. We are just trying to spread out the crowd to keep the line moving. If Thursday doesn't work at all for you, you'll have to make arrangements to have someone else pick them up.

8:00-9:00. A-F

9:00-10:00. G-L

10:00-11:00 M-R

11:00 - 12:00. S-Z

Please let me know if you have any questions!!

This weekend Spartan Speech competed at the Walnut Hills Speech competition at CAM. We competed in 12 events and took 5 to the final round. The team trophied in all events that went to the finals! Kami Waymire received 1st place in Solo Musical Theatre and Improv. Sarah Marshall received 2nd place in Improv. Jessie Marshall received 3rd place in Poetry and Imagen Gessert received 3rd place in Spontaneous Speaking. The team came in 5th out of 16 teams and we were the smallest school there. Congratulations to the entire Spartan Speech team.
Photo Credit to Donna Gessert.

post_text:
Tiffany Mulligan and Lisa Drier completed their STEM Innovator® Teacher Certification, they now have more skills to infuse innovation and the entrepreneurial mindset into their classrooms. STEM Innovator® engages students in solving authentic, community-driven, real-world problems by working in multidisciplinary teams. STEM Innovator® students learn to identify a problem of interest, verify and validate the problem through customer discovery, and establish and implement a solution. Along the way, students explore multiple careers and gain the skills to be college and career ready.
Congratulations to Lisa and Tiffany! Way to show your Spartan Pride!

post_text: Exira-EHK advance to State in First Lego League Competition this Saturday January 18 at ISU. We welcome our Spartan fans to the event. Please wish the team good luck this week!!! Our team members were students Jacey Smith, Anna Potts, Iryland McCarthy, Shelbi Partridge, Alex Hansen, Gideon King, Harlee Fahn, Josh Nelson, Gracie Olsen, Brayden Burnison. The students are engaged in this amazing STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering & Math) opportunity. First LEGO League is the most accessible, guided, global robotics competition, helping students and teachers to build a better future together. The program was built around theme-based Challenges (this year’s theme called City Shaper) to engage children in research, problem solving, coding, and engineering. The foundation of the program is the First Core Values, which emphasize teamwork, discovery, and innovation. Students emerge more confident, excited, and equipped with the skills they need in a changing workforce.

1. ISASP (This is the test that has replace Iowa

November 11, 2019 at 4:29 PM ·

Canned Food Drive for Local Food Banks!

Canned Food Drive
November 14th - 22nd

Support our local food pantries.

Food Scoring guide:

Canned goods - 1 point each
Boxed goods - 2 points each
Peanut Butter - 3 points per jar
Paper Products - 4 points
Diapers - 5 points
Monetary donations - 2 points per dollar

Seminar classes will compete with each other in the HS.
MS grade levels will compete against each other.

Student Council Members will collect goods each day, tally the points, update the leader boards, and then build a Spartan Pride Tower of Power!

Winners will receive an ice cream party

post_text: The Exira-EHK HS TAG students competed in the State Knowledge Bowl finals. The top 12 teams in their respective divisions was held at DMACC, in Ankeny, to determine the winners in a day filled with head to head, academic competition. The Knowledge Bowl Competition questions dealt with English, grammar, novels, science, math, technology, history, politics, medicine and sports & leisure! The Spartan Varsity Team players who competed Kamryn Waymire,Tyler Petersen, Lauren Hansen, Cooper Larsen and Erin Irlmeier, (left to right in the picture). “Our HS team did amazingly well this year by qualifying for the DMACC Knowledge Bowl Honors finals held on Thursday, October 24th, at DMACC in Ankeny. I am so proud of these students who represented Exira-EHK Schools in the academic tournament. “expressed Lisa Dreier, HS TAG Instructor and Quiz Bowl Club sponsor

shared_text:
Exira-EHK Schools
October 20, 2019 at 8:14 PM ·

On Thursday, Oct. 24th the elementary building is hosting an assembly. The assembly is sponsored by the Lion's Club and is inviting the community to join us. We will be starting at 8:30 am in the Elementary gym in Exira. After the assembly each grade will be visiting with our guest.

So are you wondering who will be visiting???

May I introduce Dawn and her Leader dog, Lady!

LEADERDOG LADY AND DAWN RUDOLPH will be our speaker on Thursday, October 24th. Lion Dawn was the recipient of 9SW Exira Lion Club in 2014. She has since become a Lion and continues to pay it forward to LeaderDog in a variety of interesting and meaningful ways to show her appreciation to LeaderDog and Lions. She comes from Hamilton, Michigan to be with us to share her life story.

Please come out listen to Dawn help us understand that Lions do truly serve!
